<m0>King church to open during Games<ql>
<m1><styl>vs,2<ql>
<ep>
<m0>  The National Park Service has signed a 99-year lease for the church where the Rev. Martin Luther King Jr. and his father preached, and will open it to visitors during the Summer Olympics. <m1> <m0>In exchange, Ebenezer Baptist Church will get land for a sanctuary next to the park service's new visitor center across the street. The civil rights leader and his father served as pastors of the church, and his mother, Alberta King, was fatally shot there during a 1974 service. The church has outgrown the building and has been seeking a new sanctuary since 1987.<ql>
<m1><styl>vs,3<ql>
