<m4>             3.000-pt rule             <m2><ql>
<m1><styl>vs,3<ql>
<m0>Orlando in top five airports<ql>
<m1><styl>vs,2<ql>
<ep>
<m0>   Among international airports, those at Manchester (England), Changi (Singapore) and Schiphol (Amsterdam) placed highest in a recent International Air Transport Association survey of on-the-ground service in 1995. Orlando (Florida) and Sydney (Australia) filled out the first five. The Narita (Tokyo) and Athens (Greece) airports received the lowest ratings, with Kennedy (New York) and Orly (Paris) also among the least satisfactory. More than 45,000 passengers were surveyed. <ql>
