<m0>Travel briefs<ql>
<m1><styl>vs,2<ql>
<ep>
<m0>   The United States Holocaust Memorial Museum, now one of Washington's leading tourist destinations, has instituted a toll-free number, (800) 400-9373, for ordering advance tickets. A service fee of $2.75 is assessed for each ticket, which itself is free . . . Princess Cruises has installed what it says is the industry's first direct ship telephone service in three of its ships. The 900 number allows callers to be connected directly to the purser's office, rather than requiring the caller to contact the INMARSAT operator or knowing the vessel ID. Cost is $8.95 per minute. <ql>
